<title>USA: Oracle to take $60 mln charge for Navio.</title>
<headline>Oracle to take $60 mln charge for Navio.</headline>
<dateline>REDWOOD SHORES, Calif. 1997-05-19</dateline>
<text>
<p>Oracle Corp. executives on Monday said the software company would take a $60 million charge, or $0.06 to $0.07 cents a share, for the acquisition of a stake in Navio Communications Inc.</p>
<p>On Monday, Oracle said it acquired much of Netscape Communications Corp's stake in Navio, a company that develops Internet-access software for devices such as television sets and video game players.</p>
<p>Financial terms of the transcation were not disclosed.</p>
<p>Oracle officials said they would take the charge in the fiscal first quarter ending August 31.</p>
